								<h1>Chinatown Community Vision Plan</h1>
                                    <audio src="/audio/en/ccvp.mp3" controls>
                                        Recording of CCVP article
                                    </audio>
								<p><br>The Chinatown Community Vision Plan (CCVP) is a long term collaborative plan between the Coalition for a Better Chinese American Community (CBCAC), 25th Ward Alderman Daniel Solis, and the Chicago Metropolitan Agency for Planning (CMAP) along with the residents of Chinatown who live and work there. <br> <br />
								The CCVP was initiated in April 2013, and community approval of the plan began in February 2015. Implementation of the plan is ongoing. <br> <br />
								A postcard survey distributed to Chinatown residents in English and Chinese was used to assess community needs. The questions assessed what community members would like to see in Chinatown, such as parks or improvements in certain areas. Of the 1,300 responses received, safety was the primary concern, along with cleanliness and transportation issues.<br> <br />
								The recommendations enclosed in the plan embody a range of areas, including education, public parks and spaces, transportation, and safety. Strategies for these areas range from coordination between various committees that are related to that area of concern to urban planning to directly changing or altering physical structures in the community. <br> <br />
								The members of this project hope the CCVP will result in a Chinatown that is strengthened by the work of the organizations involved in the plan. </p>
